========,1,preface.
Vestre Slidre is a municipality in Oppland county, Norway.
It is part of the traditional region of Valdres.
The administrative centre of the municipality is the village of Slidre.
The old municipality of Slidre was divided into "Vestre Slidre" and "Øystre Slidre" in 1849.
========,2,General information.
========,3,Name.
The municipality (originally the parish) is named after the old "Slidre" farm (Old Norse: "Slíðrar"), since the first church was built here.
The name is probably derived from "slíðr" which means "sheath" (which is probably referring to a long depression near the church).
The meaning of the name "Vestre Slidre" is "(the) western (part of) Slidre" (since the parish and municipality of Slidre was divided in 1849.)
========,2,History.
High above Slidre there is an ancient burial ground called the Garberg site.
At this site, there is a runestone which reads "I Godguest wrote the runes".
This stone is known as the Einang stone.
